The paper deals with decision procedures for infinite words, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). The paper also involves the study of properties of the Tribonacci word, which is a well-known example of a Sturmian word, a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.DS). The use of decision procedures and automata theory suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves the study of patterns and occurrences in the Tribonacci word, which is a topic in combinatorics (cs.LO).
